"For many years, the role of network security has focused largely on data, both in transit and at rest. But recent events are playing their role in highlighting another data security issue for the corporation – that of the threat to voice data. It was UK Prime Minister Harold Macmillan who, when asked what concerned him the most, replied: “Events my dear boy, events”. Now network security managers know what he means, as voice security has been forced onto the agenda."
